  "texts": [
    "For each group, we used a third-party expert network to recruit four subject-matter experts.",
    "The 4 selected experts had a range of professional backgrounds (e.g., journalists, academics, civil rights lawyers) but had demonstrated expertise in gender-or identity-based harms against minority groups.",
    "Each expert was tasked with compiling a list of themes and examples of toxic, hateful, or inflammatory language towards the group they were assigned to.",
    "Examples of themes provided include negative stereotypes and the use of dehumanisation language, such as characterising Latina/o/x people in the US as \"illegals\" or implying that South-East Asian Americans have poor physical hygiene.",
    "Sample 'human'-chatbot interactions were then generated via automatic red teaming 72 -where one chatbot adversarially probes another chatbot-to collect relevant conversation samples 66."
